<br>
You're in a fight, you try to use the special, and it says, &quot;You must be in fight mode to use this, please check the item description&quot;<br>
<br>
Sometimes it happens, and sometimes it doesn't. Sometimes if you try again right away, it works the second or third time. Sometimes the first attempt seems to lock the MA skill as though it had actually worked.<br>
<br>
This all started when FC decided to add this &quot;must be in a fight&quot; requirement to all MA specials. AS USUAL, funcom tried to fix a non-existent problem, (exploits my ass), and screwed up a previously-working portion of the game.<br>
<br>
More quality software from the steely-eyed missilemen at Funcom... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ucrimhawk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crimhawk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>They call me Bruce.</span><br>  Posts: 353<br> <font color=#660000>(7/23/02 1:29:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2073.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bright, Blue, Cloudless Sky</span><hr size=1> How was starting off a fight with your special attack deemed an exploit? I have tried to imagine every possible way it might be exploitable to start a fight with a special and draw a blank every time. Can someone fill me in on this plz. Oh, and I've noticed that I can't use my Brawl skill as fast as it recharges because more often than not I get the &quot;Wait for previous special atttack to finish&quot; message. Any clue why this is happening? Thanks all.<br>
<br>
Hawk <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/uiccusion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>iccusion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#660000>(7/23/02 2:54:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2073.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bright, Blue, Cloudless Sky</span><hr size=1> Specials like Brawl, Fast Attack, Burst, Fling, etc, have all been &quot;disconnected&quot; from the server. In the old days, I believe the status of these specials was constantly communicated to the client with each packet of info from the server. That way, your client PC was IMMEDIATELY updated whenever the special was again available, since the lock is monitored on the server (to prevent client-side hacks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ), and the icon was only enabled when the server passed that info back to the client.<br>
<br>
However, I believe this has changed in an effort to streamline network traffic and thereby reduce lag. I think the client-side application now just disables the icon and then starts a simple &quot;timer&quot; after the special is used. If that special has a 15 second refresh (for example), in exactly 15 seconds the AO client re-enables the special's icon without any info from the server (thus saving network traffic). Unfortunately, the client has no actual idea whether or not that special is really available on the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   server</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> yet. All it knows is that the specified amount of time has passed at the player's PC, so it's time to turn the icon back on again. When you take into account ping time, possible packet loss and server-side lag, it may be several seconds until the server will actually permit the special to be re-triggered. So when you hit your newly enabled Brawl key (for example), the client sends a Brawl request to the server in the next packet. I imagine it goes something like this:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   Crimhawk sees a Veteran Thug in the next room, and bravely rushes in to engage.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Player:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Take that, Veteran Thug! <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &lt;hits Brawl key&gt;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Client:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> [To server] Crimhawk has Brawled that thug! <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &lt;Deactivates brawl icon, and starts 15 second client-side Brawl timer&gt;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Server:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Gotcha. Initiating combat with the thug. Here's that Brawl damage: 1502. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &lt;Starts SERVER-side Brawl timer&gt;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Client:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> &quot;You hit Veteran Thug for 1502 pts of Brawl damage.&quot;<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &lt;Fight continues for approximately 15 seconds&gt;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Player:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Ouch...this guy hits hard...hurry up and recycle, Brawl! <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &lt;punches Brawl key repeatedly even though it is still greyed out...&gt;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Client:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &lt;15 second client-side brawl timer expires, so Brawl icon is re-enabled&gt;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> &quot;Brawl skill available.&quot;<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Player:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Yes! <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &lt;Hits the now-active Brawl key with authority&gt;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Client:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> [To server] Crimhawk wants to Brawl again. Sounds good to me! Whaddya say?<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Server:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Nope. Skill is still locked. Not yet.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Client:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> &quot;Wait for previous special atttack to finish&quot;<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Player:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Dammit! <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &lt;Hits the still-active Brawl key again&gt;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Client:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> [To server] Crimhawk wants to Brawl again. Sounds good to me! Whaddya say?<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Server:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Nope. Skill is still locked. Not yet...<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Client:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> &quot;Wait for previous special atttack to finish&quot;<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Server:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &lt;Server-side Brawl timer expires&gt;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Player:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Arrrrgh! <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &lt;Hits Brawl key repeatedly while watching his health drop...&gt;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Client:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Crimhawk wants to Brawl again. Sounds good to me! Whaddya say?<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Server:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> OK. Here's that Brawl damage: 1247, plus stun.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Client:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> &quot;You hit Veteran Thug for 1247 pts of Brawl damage.&quot; <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  &lt;displays stun effect on mob&gt;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
etc.<br>
<br>
I believe this is what is happening.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   &quot;How was starting off a fight with your special attack deemed an exploit? I have tried to imagine every possible way it might be exploitable to start a fight with a special and draw a blank every time.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I'm not really sure what the exploit was either, but if the target was in the range of the MA special attack (say, BwT, for example), it may have been possible to do the MA special damage without initiating combat. For example, you can't start combat when swimming, right? What if there was high level mob swimming at the edge of the water, and you walked up to him and hit BwT? You might be able to do damage without actually getting attacked. *shrug* Or what if there were an obstruction between you and the mob? I think LOS rules don't apply to specials the same way as regular attacks (I believe the specials just use range), so it might have been possible to hit someone with BwT, initiate combat, but not have the mob able to hit back. Then you keep hitting BwT as it refreshes and kill the mob with no risk. This is a total guess on my part, but I bet something <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   like</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> this is what they are trying to avoid.<br>
<br>
