<br>
I'll tell you what the exploit is...kind of.  Dont want to get FC mad at me or have everyone exploiting if they revert back to the way old MA specials were handled before this patch.<br>
<br>
Before this patch there was a way to  perform a certain MA special attack on a mob, in such a way as the mob was not able to attack back.  You could just reattack the mob until he was dead.  <br>
<br>
Clearly an exploit, one that only a worthless worm of an MA would use.  But I'm sure there were some out there that might try to use every chance they had.<br>
<br>
It is kind of like the way a soldier is trying to attack a mob in a mission, but the only damge the mob takes is Burst.  Later on you find out that the mob you were attacking is not where he appears on the screen at all, and may be in a completely different room.  <br>
<br>
Also similar to when a team member is being attacked by a mob, that no one can see, including the guy getting his A$$ kicked.  You do a /assist on your buddy and hit &quot;Q&quot;, and start blasting the mob with normal attacks, but in this case your specials don't work, the game says &quot;No line of sight&quot;.<br>
<br>
So, there are wierd glitchy bugs in this game, and every patch seems to bring new ones.  Funcom is trying to fix them, but every new patch brings new quirky ones. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ulordfozzy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>LordFozzy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Ninja Wanna-Be</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#660000>(7/24/02 8:35:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2073.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bright, Blue, Cloudless Sky</span><hr size=1> LOL you'll get there Crimhawk!<br>
